cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a novel algorithm for learning the topology and estimating the parameters of a distribution grid using minimal observational requirements. This involves using voltage and injection measurements at the terminal nodes of the grid to reconstruct the topology and impedances of the operational lines. This problem involves aspects of systems engineering (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and computer engineering (cs.CE).
